1. DEFINITION OF A SPELL

Spell (S)
A constrained linguistic sequence that produces a predictable, bounded change in a target state vector.

Formally:
S = \{L, P, \Delta N, \Sigma_C\}

Where:
	‚Ä¢	L = Linguistic pattern (text, metaphor, poem, ritual language)
	‚Ä¢	P = Procedure (sequencing rules, timing, tempo, cadence)
	‚Ä¢	ŒîN = Desired nervous-system or cognitive state shift
	‚Ä¢	Œ£C = Ethics floor ensuring safety

‚∏ª

2. STATE VECTOR MODEL

PantheonOS defines the target of any spell as a State Vector:

\text{StateVector} = (A, E, V, M, R)
	‚Ä¢	A = Autonomic tone (sympathetic/parasympathetic)
	‚Ä¢	E = Emotional valence
	‚Ä¢	V = Arousal / tempo
	‚Ä¢	M = Meaning alignment (NTE projection)
	‚Ä¢	R = Risk profile (Hound + Arctic Loop)

Spells do not ‚Äúchange the person.‚Äù
They shift the vector.

